President Donald Trump addressed a crowd at the Sheffer Corporation in Blue Ash, Ohio, where he spoke about the success of the recently passed tax cuts and the positive impact they have had on American workers and businesses. He highlighted the benefits of the tax cuts, including higher paychecks, lower taxes, and the return of jobs and manufacturing to the United States. Trump also criticized Democrats, particularly Nancy Pelosi, for opposing the tax cuts and not supporting the military. He emphasized the importance of job creation and the fight against the drug epidemic, and praised the hard work and dedication of American workers. Trump was joined by several business leaders who shared how the tax cuts have allowed them to invest in their employees and businesses.